CSS - 10 Grid - layout

<style>
  #grid{
    border:5px solid pink;
    display:grid;
    grid-template-columns: 150px(*first) 1fr(*rest of them);
  }

  div{
    border:5px solid gray;
  }
</style>

<body>
  <div id="grid"> *value - you can decide whatever you want)
    <div>NAVIGATION</div>
    <div>ARTICLE</div>
  </div>
</body>


  CSS - 12 Media Query ; Responsive Web (when you make narrow of web then all the letter or
  picture also make in proper size following pixel)
<style>
  div{
    border;10px; solid green;
    font-size:60px;
  }

  @media(min-width:800px)
    div{
      display:none;   *Do not show on display
    }
</style>
<body>
  <div>
    Responsive
  </div>
</body>
